HEADWORD: Acicular
<hw>A*cic"u*lar</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Needle-shaped;
slender like a needle or bristle, as some leaves or crystals; also,
having sharp points like needles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><wordforms><wf>A*cic"u*lar*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>.⟦br⟧
